Jenkins pipeline variable, post build action 

DAY 19

PIPELINE: VARIABLE

VARIABLES:
Assigning value
$a = 10$
$name = raham$
$a$ is the variable, $10$ is the value.
	1. USER DEFINED VARIABLE
a. local variable: We can define inside the job.
b. global variable: We can define outside jobs.
	2. JENKINS ENV. VARIABLE
They are going to change as per build.

HOW TO PASS VARIABLES ON PIPELINE
HOW TO PASS VARIABLE IN THE JOB
Groovy

pipeline {
    agent any
    environment {
        name = "raham"
        loc = "Nigeria"
    }
    stages {
        stage ('one') {
            steps {
                echo "Hi my name is ${name} and I'm from ${loc}"
                sh 'env'
            }
        }
    }
}
HOW TO DEFINE OUTSIDE THE JOB
Manage Jenkins -> System -> Global Properties -> Fill in Name & Value -> Save

POST BUILD ACTIONS
Actions that we perform after the build.
Types
	• Always: If build fail or successful, it will run post actions.
	• Success: Execute build only when successful.
	• Failure: Execute build when build fails.
SAMPLE
Groovy

pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage ('one') {
            steps {
                sh 'env'
            }
        }
    }
    post {
        always {
            echo "the build is done"
        }
    }
}
